{"title_page": "Claudio Bravo (footballer, born 1997)", "text_new": "{{short description|Argentinian association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n\n{{For|the Chilean goalkeeper|Claudio Bravo}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Claudio Bravo\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Claudio Nicol\u00e1s Bravo\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1997|3|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Lomas de Zamora]], Argentina\n| height         = {{height|m=1.79}}\n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub    = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]]\n| clubnumber     = 3\n| youthyears1    =           |youthclubs1 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]]\n| years1         = 2016\u2013     |clubs1 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]]  |caps1 = 25          |goals1 = 0\n| nationalyears1 =           |nationalteam1 =                               |nationalcaps1 =     |nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update    = 23:26, 30 March 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n| medaltemplates =\n}}\n\n'''Claudio Nicol\u00e1s Bravo''' (born 13 March 1997) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite news|title=Argentina - C. Bravo|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/claudio-nicolas-bravo/432205/|accessdate=30 September 2018|work=Soccerway}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nBravo began his career with [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref name=\"BDFA\">{{cite news|title=Ficha Estadistica de CLAUDIO BRAVO|url=http://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugadores-CLAUDIO-NICOLAS-BRAVO-105539.html|accessdate=30 September 2018|work=BDFA}}</ref> He was an unused substitute once during the [[2016 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] season, which preceded his senior professional debut arriving on 24 September 2017 as Banfield scored four unanswered goals versus [[Rosario Central]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/> Eight further appearances followed in [[2017\u201318 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2017\u201318]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/> He featured in continental football for the first time in July 2018, playing the full duration of a loss to [[Boston River]].<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref name=\"Uno Santa Fe\">{{cite news|title=Uni\u00f3n derrot\u00f3 a Banfield y sue\u00f1a con jugar su primer torneo internacional|url=https://www.unosantafe.com.ar/ovacion/union-derroto-a-banfield-y-suena-con-jugar-su-primer-torneo-internacional-03192018_rJX-k3dnwm|accessdate=30 September 2018|work=Uno Santa Fe|date=19 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nIn November 2015, Bravo was selected to train with the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20s]] under manager [[Humberto Grondona]].<ref name=\"Banfield\">{{cite news|title=Los juveniles de Banfield Claudio Bravo y Franco Vivas fueron citados nuevamente para entrenar con la Selecci\u00f3n|url=https://twitter.com/cab_oficial/status/664525826306781184|accessdate=30 September 2018|work=Banfield|date=11 November 2015}}</ref> September 2019 saw Bravo receive a call-up to the [[Argentina national under-23 football team|U23s]] for a friendly with Bolivia.<ref name=\"AFA1\">{{cite news|title=La Selecci\u00f3n Sub 23 jugar\u00e1 ante Bolivia desde las 19, en el estadio de Banfield|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield|accessdate=4 September 2019|work=AFA|date=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|30 September 2018}}.<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Club statistics\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Copa Argentina]]</ref>\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<ref group=\"lower-alpha\">Includes the [[Copa Libertadores]] and [[Copa Sudame